{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0a1b1640-5ca2-478b-b146-fbf87f67fd92","content":"Your project uses MSTest 3.8 on Microsoft.Testing.Platform. The best way to detect hanging tests is with the **HangDump** extension — it will capture a dump identifying the stuck test after a timeout.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_MRatNLkUKPLmPJnlQlKqDY","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Adding hang dump extension"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_WQPrW2bOHdpyxOZeZukpx5","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-e6cfaab7e9384ccbb447b4d0e31c2088/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />","new_str":"    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.0\" />\n    <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump\" Version=\"1.6.2\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-e6cfaab7e9384ccbb447b4d0e31c2088/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"19646dfb-c714-4d8c-902f-09d94892a1d9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is using MSTest 3.8.0 with Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) runner. They want to add a hang timeout of 5 minutes.\n\nWith MSTest on MTP, hang detection is available via the `--hangdump` extension or through the `[Timeout]` attribute. But for a global hang timeout that detects which test is hanging, the best approach is to use the MTP hang dump feature.\n\nFor MSTest with MTP, you can:\n\n1. Add the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` NuGet package\n2. Run tests with `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\n\n3. Alternatively, set a global timeout using MSTest's `[Timeout]` attribute or `.runsettings` file\n\nThe HangDump extension is the most effective option here since it creates a diagnostic dump when tests hang, making it easier to identify which test is causing the issue.","outputTokens":532},"id":"8901b102-1ba9-43b7-8c4b-4d92c9952247","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:16:40.243Z","parentId":"55cf27c0-aafb-450d-992c-af820dea